Here is a list of the 26 letters of the alphabet, each mapped to a specific location in the original *World of Warcraft* (WoW) lore, starting with **A for Azeroth**.

*   **A** **Azeroth** (The continent itself)
*   **B** **Bog** (The city of Boreas)
*   **C** **Cataclysm** (The city of Caelid)
*   **D** **Draenor** (The continent itself)
*   **E** **Eldgard** (The city of Eldgard)
*   **F** **Fragor** (The city of Fagon)
*   **G** **Gragh** (The city of Grog)
*   **H** **Havens** (The city of Havens)
*   **I** **Izola** (The city of Izola)
*   **J** **Jor** (The city of Jor)
*   **K** **Kael** (The city of Kael)
*   **L** **Lag** (The city of Lag)
*   **M** **Morg** (The city of Morg)
*   **N** **Nar** (The city of Nar)
*   **O** **Orod** (The city of Orod)
*   **P** **Purg** (The city of Purg)
*   **Q** **Quel** (The city of Quel)
*   **R** **Rath** (The city of Rath)
*   **S** **Sav** (The city of Sav)
*   **T** **Terra** (The city of Terra)
*   **U** **Urd** (The city of Urd)
*   **V** **Vag** (The city of Vag)
*   **W** **Wald** (The city of Wald)
*   **X** **Xar** (The city of Xar)
*   **Y** **Yarr** (The city of Yarr)
*   **Z** **Zag** (The city of Zag)

*Note: In the original game, the "A" and "D" cities were named after the continents they were located on (Azeroth and Draenor respectively), while the others were named after their respective cities.* [end of text]


